\begin_layout Subsubsection*
a) Show that the model defined above corresponds to what Lande calls the
 ‘psychophysical’ model of mating preferences
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Starting with equation [9] from Lande:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{S}{\sigma^{2}}=\beta=\frac{\frac{1}{\alpha}\bar{y}-\left[1+\frac{\epsilon}{\alpha}\right]\bar{z}+\theta}{\omega^{2}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Filling in 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=\frac{1}{\omega^{2}}$
\end_inset

 yields the equation on the document:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\beta=\frac{\omega^{2}\bar{y}-\bar{z}+\theta}{\omega^{2}}=\frac{\omega^{2}\bar{y}-\bar{z}+\theta}{\omega^{2}}=\frac{\omega^{2}\bar{y}}{\omega^{2}}-\frac{\bar{z}+\theta}{\omega^{2}}=\bar{y}-\frac{\bar{z}+\theta}{\omega^{2}}=\beta_{z}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
b) Give a biological interpretation for the parameters θ and ω , and explain
 why there is a factor 1⁄2 in front of the G-matrix in equation (1).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $θ$
\end_inset

: male trait value with highest viability, the optimal trait value without
 sexual selection.
 For example, the most optimal tail length.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $ω$
\end_inset

: range of male phenotypes around the optimum for high viability, the strength
 of the effect on viability when a trait deviates from the optimum.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $ω$
\end_inset

 is infinite, all trait values result in the same (optimal) viability, if
 
\begin_inset Formula $ω$
\end_inset

 is close to zero, only males close the 
\begin_inset Formula $θ$
\end_inset

 have a high viability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

: the effect of allele change for the male trait happens within males only,
 that is, in half of the sexes.
 Also, the alleles for the female preference are only actively changed within
 females
\end_layout

